# Scholar Soul — Example
# This is an example file. Copy to memory/soul.md and fill in your details.
# CONSTITUTION §8: The live file is gitignored. Only this .example is committed.
# Populated during onboarding (00_onboarding.md, Phase 2 + Phase 3).

---

## Identity

name: "Your Full Name"
school: "School of CSE / CSA"
batch_year: YYYY
registration_date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
research_domain: ""
# Example: "Machine Learning for Healthcare" or "IoT Security"

---

## Career Aspiration

career_goal: ""
# Where do you see yourself after the PhD?
# Example: "Industry research at a tech company", "Faculty at a Tier-1 institution", "Startup founder"

career_timeline: ""
# When do you want to be in this role?
# Example: "Within 2 years of PhD completion"

---

## Learning & Communication

learning_style: ""
# Options: visual | conceptual | hands-on | reading-first | mixed | collaborative

communication_preference: ""
# Options: conversational | structured | brief | detailed | Socratic

preferred_session_length: ""
# Example: "30 minutes focused, then break" or "long exploratory sessions"

---

## Core Strengths

strengths: []
# List 3–5 things you are genuinely good at (technical or otherwise)
# Example: ["systems thinking", "Python and data pipelines", "communicating complex ideas simply"]

---

## Acknowledged Challenges

challenges: []
# List 2–3 things you know you find difficult in research or academic life
# This is private — it helps the agent calibrate its support
# Example: ["perfectionism — hard to submit until it feels perfect", "writing takes me a long time"]

---

## Primary Motivators

motivators: []
# What drives you to keep going on hard days?
# Example: ["wanting to improve outcomes for rural students", "proving something to myself", "love of the problem"]

---

## Acknowledged Fears

fears: []
# Private. What worries you about this PhD journey?
# Example: ["running out of time", "guide relationship becoming difficult", "imposter syndrome"]

---

## Notes from Guide

guide_notes: ""
# Optional: any specific things your guide has asked you to focus on or improve
